    {
      "@id": "urn:pharmagent:dm-boite-a-outil:excerpt:061",
      "@type": "pharm:SourceExcerpt",
      "name": "DM-boite-a-outil - extrait 61",
      "description": "## Boîte à outils - ajustement des antidiabétiques ## Surveillance du glucose en continue (Free Style Libre et Dexcom G6) Sources : Vigersky RA, McMahon C. The Relationship of Hemoglobin A1C to Time-in-Range in Patients with Diabetes. Diabetes Technology &amp; Therapeutics. [En ligne]. 2019. [cité 14 déc 2021]; 21(2):81 -5. Disponible : https://www.liebertpub.com/doi/10.1089/dia.2018.0310 Kalergis M, Nadeau J, Pacaud D, Yared Z, Yale J-F. Accuracy and Reliability of Reporting Self-monitoring of Blood Glucose Results in Adults With Type 1 and Type 2 Diabetes. Canadian Journal of Diabetes. [En ligne]. 2006. [cité 14 déc 2021]; 30(3):241 -7. Disponible : [https://www.canadianjournalofdiabetes.com/article/S1499-2671(06)03006-1/fulltext#relatedArticles](https://www.canadianjournalofdiabetes.com/article/S1499-2671(06)03006-1/fulltext#relatedArticles) Guerrero-García C, Rubio-Guerra AF. Combination therapy in the treatment of hypertension. Drugs Context. [En ligne]. 2018. [cité 14 déc 2021]; 7:212531. Disponible : [https://care.diabetesjournals.org/content/42/8/1593](https://care.diabetesjournals.org/content/42/8/1593) Surveillance flash du glucose. Professionnels de la santé [En ligne]. 2021. [cité 14 déc 2021]. Disponible : [https://provider.freestyle.abbott/ca-fr/accueil/surveillance-flash-du-glucose.html](https://provider.freestyle.abbott/ca-fr/accueil/surveillance-flash-du-glucose.html) [https://provider.freestyle.abbott/content/dam/adc/provider/countries/ca-en/pdfs/ADC-34254-ART-01-of-0](https://provider.freestyle.abbott/content/dam/adc/provider/countries/ca-en/pdfs/ADC-3425",
      "sourceDocument": {
        "@id": "urn:pharmagent:dm-boite-a-outil:doc"
      },
      "sourcePage": "unknown",
      "sourceSection": "Boîte à outils - ajustement des antidiabétiques",
      "sourceQuote": "## Boîte à outils - ajustement des antidiabétiques ## Surveillance du glucose en continue (Free Style Libre et Dexcom G6) Sources : Vigersky RA, McMahon C. The Relationship of Hemoglobin A1C to Time-in-Range in Patients with Diabetes. Diabetes Technology &amp; Therapeutics. [En ligne]. 2019. [cité 14 déc 2021]; 21(2):81 -5. Disponible : https://www.liebertpub.com/doi/10.1089/dia.2018.0310 Kalergis M, Nadeau J, Pacaud D, Yared Z, Yale J-F. Accuracy and Reliability of Reporting Self-monitoring of Blood Glucose Results in Adults With Type 1 and Type 2 Diabetes. Canadian Journal of Diabetes. [En ligne]. 2006. [cité 14 déc 2021]; 30(3):241 -7. Disponible : [https://www.canadianjournalofdiabetes.com/article/S1499-2671(06)03006-1/fulltext#relatedArticles](https://www.canadianjournalofdiabetes.com/article/S1499-2671(06)03006-1/fulltext#relatedArticles) Guerrero-García C, Rubio-Guerra AF. Combination therapy in the treatment of hypertension. Drugs Context. [En ligne]. 2018. [cité 14 déc 2021]; 7:212531. Disponible : [https://care.diabetesjournals.org/content/42/8/1593](https://care.diabetesjournals.org/content/42/8/1593) Surveillance flash du glucose. Professionnels de la santé [En ligne]. 2021. [cité 14 déc 2021]. Disponible : [https://provider.freestyle.abbott/ca-fr/accueil/surveillance-flash-du-glucose.html](https://provider.freestyle.abbott/ca-fr/accueil/surveillance-flash-du-glucose.html) [https://provider.freestyle.abbott/content/dam/adc/provider/countries/ca-en/pdfs/ADC-34254-ART-01-of-0](https://provider.freestyle.abbott/content/dam/adc/provider/countries/ca-en/pdfs/ADC-3425",
